y as one of the benchmarks for understanding the energy distribution of the first supernova in the Universe. ESO ID 107.22SJ; based on observations made with ESO VLT at the La Silla Paranal observatory under programmes ID 107.22SJ, 0101.B-0189, and 0101.D-0210, as well as on data obtained from the ESO Science Archive Facility.},
